title: "YARA - Snort For Files"
---

Yara is a great product not only for security researchers. <br>
Using this tool you can identify and classify files(PE files, text files, etc.) based on patterns. <br>
The tool is easy to use. We can create a.k.a rules(name.yar) which consist set of rules. We can create a rule like this: <br>

{% highlight c %}
rule first_or_second
{
        strings:
               $a = "first_string"  // comment
               $b = "second_string" nocase // Yara is case-sensitive by default
        condition:
               $a or $b
}
{% endhighlight %}

Execute: <br>
{% highlight bash %}
yara xxx.yar xxx.file
{% endhighlight %}

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

Everything in this example is very intuitive. If the file contains strings $a or $b, Yara can detect this. <br>

Also, we use hexadecimal strings or use regular expressions: <br>
{% highlight c %}
rule reg_hex
{
            strings:
                 $rg = /state: (on|off)/
                 $hx = { E8 00 ?? A1 }
            condition:
                 $rg and $hx
                 filesize > 500KB
}
{% endhighlight %}
Yes, there are some helpful keywords too.<br>

We can create more interesting rules, for example, we can detect files which contain macro codes.<br>
Source: https://github.com/Yara-Rules/rules/ <br>
{% highlight c %}
rule Contains_VBA_macro_code
{
    meta:
        author = "evild3ad"
        description = "Detect a MS Office document with embedded VBA macro code"
        date = "2016-01-09"
        filetype = "Office documents"

    strings:
        $officemagic = { D0 CF 11 E0 A1 B1 1A E1 }
        $zipmagic = "PK"

        $97str1 = "_VBA_PROJECT_CUR" wide
        $97str2 = "VBAProject"
        $97str3 = { 41 74 74 72 69 62 75 74 00 65 20 56 42 5F } // Attribute VB_

        $xmlstr1 = "vbaProject.bin"
        $xmlstr2 = "vbaData.xml"

    condition:
        ($officemagic at 0 and any of ($97str*)) or ($zipmagic at 0 and any of ($xmlstr*))
}
{% endhighlight %}

Also, you can convert ClamAV rules. For more detailed and updated information you should see this doc: https://yara.readthedocs.io
